docs {
  Compute degree centrality (in-degree, out-degree, total)
  for nodes in the collection, sorted by total degree.

  Nodes with high degree are well-connected hubs. For the
  Alice/Bob/Atlas example, Alice and Project Atlas should
  have the highest degree since they participate in the
  most relationships.

  Does not require GDS â€” uses plain Cypher aggregation.
}
